title: For Sale:   Smith & Wesson 439 9mm Parabellum Handgun with Two FREE Magazines, an 8 round and 9 round clip!
postcontent:
This Model 439 is a well-cared-for family protection weapon and private collector's piece. It is no longer in production, so they are harder to find, but it is a well-crafted, well-balanced weapon. Many models were sold during production, but they are fast disappearing into collector's hands. The Karabiner Model 1931 (K31) is a magazine-fed, straight-pull bolt-action rifle. It was the standard issue rifle of the Swiss armed forces from 1933 until 1958, though examples remained in service into the 1970s. It has a 6-round removable magazine, and is chambered for the 7.5x55mm Swiss (also known as Gewehrpatrone 1911, GP11, or unofficially 7.5x55mm Schmidt Rubin), a cartridge with ballistic qualities similar to the 7.62x51mm NATO/.308 Winchester cartridge. Each rifle included a 6 round detachable box magazine with matching engraved serial number. A stripper clip loads the magazine from the top of the receiver.
